defaultSwitchMode.name: defaultSwitchMode
defaultSwitchMode.description: Default switch mode. This is used by the object portSwitchMode when it's value is default(1)

defaultFlowControlMode.name: defaultFlowControlMode
defaultFlowControlMode.description: Default Flow Control mode. This is used by the object portConfFlowControl when it's value is default(1)

localManagementTimeout.name: localManagementTimeout
localManagementTimeout.description: The time (in minutes) that has elapsed before a local management session (telnet or serial) closes when it has not been used. The value '0' means no timeout.

temperatureLevel.name: temperatureLevel
temperatureLevel.description: temperatureLevel values: normal(1) : Temperature normal high(2) : Temperature high. Check air circulation critical(3): Temperature critical. Shut down in 30 seconds

redundantPowerSupplyStatus.name: redundantPowerSupplyStatus
redundantPowerSupplyStatus.description: Status for redundant power supply: notPresent(1): RPS not connected or failed. (It may be present but not plugged in or damaged etc.) present(2): RPS not active. (It may be present, connected, in perfect health, but just not being used.) active(3): RPS active

portMirroring.name: portMirroring
portMirroring.description: enable(1): Enabling of port mirroring. This is only possible if RMON is disabled. disable(2): Disabling of port mirroring. RMON can only be enabled if port mirroring is disabled

disableRmon.name: disableRmon
disableRmon.description: destroyAll(1): Disable RMON and destroy all probes. This is necessary for enabling port mirroring

isRmonActive.name: isRmonActive
isRmonActive.description: enabled(1): RMON is enabled disabled(2): RMON is disabled

switchTotalTraffic.name: switchTotalTraffic
switchTotalTraffic.description: Total switch traffic measured in octets

bufferPoolUsed.name: bufferPoolUsed
bufferPoolUsed.description: Total switch buffer pool usage. (percentage between 0 and 100)

featuresBitFlag.name: featuresBitFlag
featuresBitFlag.description: Bit field index from bit 1 to 32. If an bit is set, the switch supports the related feature. BIT 1: Distributed VLAN BIT 2: Layer 3 switching BIT 3: Diagnostics BIT 4: RSVP BIT 5: IP multicast BIT 6: IP filtering BIT 7: ATM STP BIT 8: Port trunking BIT 9: Port mirroring BIT 10: VLAN stacking BIT 11: Forwarding of learn packets BIT 12: IGMP pruning BIT 13: ToS BIT 14: Bulk En-/Disable STP BIT 15: VLAN table flush BIT 16: Transparent Cache BIT 17: Compressed Stack

ownMatrixAttachmentPort.name: ownMatrixAttachmentPort
ownMatrixAttachmentPort.description: Returns the port number of the Matrix port the switch is attached to. NB: will return 50 for a switch not connected to a Matrix Module

stackCrc.name: stackCrc
stackCrc.description: checksum for stack specific parameters If a parameter is unavailable 0 is returned

portSnmpPort.name: portSnmpPort
portSnmpPort.description: Returns the port which this SNMP request went through. This gives the port on which the SNMP management system is connected.

portLastChange.name: portLastChange
portLastChange.description: The value of sysUpTime after any interface has changed state

portInfoTable.name: portInfoTable
portInfoTable.description: Port information table which includes all ports.

portInfoIndex.name: portInfoIndex
portInfoIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an interface. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

portInfoType.name: portInfoType
portInfoType.description: The type of Physical interface at the port.

portConfEntry.name: portConfEntry
portConfEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuration and status of a port.

portConfIndex.name: portConfIndex
portConfIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an interface. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

portConfDescr.name: portConfDescr
portConfDescr.description: User configurable description of the port.

portConfLocation.name: portConfLocation
portConfLocation.description: User configurable location of the port.

portConfConfigSwitchMode.name: portConfConfigSwitchMode
portConfConfigSwitchMode.description: Port Switch mode. If set to default(1) the value from defaultSwitchMode is used.

portConfFlowControl.name: portConfFlowControl
portConfFlowControl.description: Port Flow Control mode. If set to default(1) the value from defaultFlowControlMode is used.

portConfSpeedSupported.name: portConfSpeedSupported
portConfSpeedSupported.description: The possible speeds of a port

portConfDuplexSupported.name: portConfDuplexSupported
portConfDuplexSupported.description: The possible duplex modes of a port

portConfConfigSpeed.name: portConfConfigSpeed
portConfConfigSpeed.description: The configured speed for a port

portConfConfigDuplex.name: portConfConfigDuplex
portConfConfigDuplex.description: The configured duplex mode for a port

portConfConfigAutoNeg.name: portConfConfigAutoNeg
portConfConfigAutoNeg.description: The configured auto-negotiation for a port

portConfSpeed.name: portConfSpeed
portConfSpeed.description: The current speed for a port

portConfDuplex.name: portConfDuplex
portConfDuplex.description: The current duplex mode for a port

portConfAutoNeg.name: portConfAutoNeg
portConfAutoNeg.description: The currect auto-negotiation for a port

portConfSwitchMode.name: portConfSwitchMode
portConfSwitchMode.description: Current forwarding mode of the port.

portConfTrunkSupported.name: portConfTrunkSupported
portConfTrunkSupported.description: The types of port trunking available for the actual port. A trunk consists of a number ports sitting next to each other. The first port is selected as master for the trunk, the following as slaves. trunkWidthTwo(1): Port is available as master for 2 port trunking. trunkWidthFour(2): Port is available as master for 4 port trunking. trunkMaster(3): Port is master in a trunk. trunkSlave(4): Port is slave in a trunk. notAvailable(99): Port is not available for trunking.

portConfTrunkConfig.name: portConfTrunkConfig
portConfTrunkConfig.description: The size of the actual trunk. 0 means trunkWidthTwo(1): This port is member of a 2 port trunk. trunkWidthFour(2):This port is member of a 4 port trunk. disable(99): This port is not trunked

portConfMirrorSupported.name: portConfMirrorSupported
portConfMirrorSupported.description: Which mode of port mirroring does the port support. mirrorSourceOnly(1): Port can only be used as source for mirroring mirrorDestinationOnly(2): Port can only be used as destination for mirroring mirrorSourceOrDestination(3): Port can be used as source or destination notAvailable(99): Port can not be used for mirroring

portConfMirrorConfig.name: portConfMirrorConfig
portConfMirrorConfig.description: The configured port mirroring for the actual port. mirrorSource(1): Port is source for mirroring mirrorDestination(2): Port is destination for mirroring disabled(99): Port is not mirrored

portConfVlanSupported.name: portConfVlanSupported
portConfVlanSupported.description: Describes if the port can be used as a port rule in the VLAN configuration. enabled(1): Port can be used in port VLANs notAvailable(99): Port can not be used in port VLANs

portAllSpanningTreeMode.name: portAllSpanningTreeMode
portAllSpanningTreeMode.description: Enable or Disable Spanning Tree Protocol for all ports on switch. SET is only allowed with value allEnabled(1) or allDisabled(2).

txStatEntry.name: txStatEntry
txStatEntry.description: An entry containing objects for transmit statistics.

txStatIndex.name: txStatIndex
txStatIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an interface. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

txOctetsIllegalAddrType.name: txOctetsIllegalAddrType
txOctetsIllegalAddrType.description: Internal error -- not possible. Always zero.

tx1ArbitFrameDelay.name: tx1ArbitFrameDelay
tx1ArbitFrameDelay.description: Tx packets delayed less than 1 slot time (due to NIMBUS overload).

tx2ArbitFrameDelay.description: Tx packets delayed between 1 and 2 slot times (due to NIMBUS overload)

tx7ArbitFrameDelay.name: tx7ArbitFrameDelay
tx7ArbitFrameDelay.description: Tx packets delayed more than 32 slot times (due to NIMBUS overload)

txDeferreds.name: txDeferreds
txDeferreds.description: Half duplex: Tx packet delayed, due to receiving a packet. Full duplex: Tx packet delayed, due to receiving of a MAC pause control frame.

txOctetsHis.description: Upper part of a 64 bit octet transmitted counter

txOctetsLos.name: txOctetsLos
txOctetsLos.description: Lower part of a 64 bit octet transmitted counter

txExcessiveDeferralsErrors.name: txExcessiveDeferralsErrors
txExcessiveDeferralsErrors.description: Maximum deferral should be the duration of a maximum length packet, if no errors on the net. Excessive deferral is indicated if deferral duration is more than approximately 49 maximum packets.

txExcessiveLengthDrops.name: txExcessiveLengthDrops
txExcessiveLengthDrops.description: Tx packets discarded due to too long packets (Only possible if receiving too long packets are allowed)

txLinkDownEvents.name: txLinkDownEvents
txLinkDownEvents.description: No link pulses are received. Usually this means that the cable is removed.

txAllCounterPackets.name: txAllCounterPackets
txAllCounterPackets.description: A collection of all counters for byte and packet counters. This object is needed to optimize SNMP traffic. The counters in this string are: txStatIndex INTEGER txOctetsHis Counter txOctetsLos Counter txUCPkts64Octets Counter txUCPkts65To127Octets Counter txUCPkts128To255Octets Counter txUCPkts256To511Octets Counter txUCPkts512To1023Octets Counter txUCPkts1024To1518Octets Counter txMCPkts64Octets Counter txMCPkts65To127Octets Counter txMCPkts128To255Octets Counter txMCPkts256To511Octets Counter txMCPkts512To1023Octets Counter txMCPkts1024To1518Octets Counter txBCPkts64Octets Counter txBCPkts65To127Octets Counter txBCPkts128To255Octets Counter txBCPkts256To511Octets Counter txBCPkts512To1023Octets Counter txBCPkts1024To1518Octets Counter The values are represented in the OCTET STRING in the listed order, each value stored as a 32 bits big engine value.

txAllCounterOthers.name: txAllCounterOthers
txAllCounterOthers.description: A collection of all counters -- other than for byte and packet counters. This object is needed to optimize SNMP traffic. The counters in this string are: txStatIndex INTEGER txDeferreds Counter txExcessiveDeferralsErrors Counter txForwRxErrorCollision Counter txNiaUnderRunAborts Counter txLinkDownEvents Counter -- Counters from RFC1643 txCSenseErrors Counter txSQEErrors Counter txLateCollisions Counter txExcessiveCollisionErrors Counter txSingleCollisionFrames Counter txMultipleCollisionFrames Counter The values are represented in the OCTET STRING in the listed order, each value stored as a 32 bits big engine value.

rxFilterMACUnexp2ndPortDrops.description: MAC address has been moved from one port to another

rxFilterIllegalMACDrops.description: Packet is dropped because the source MAC address is illegal (zero or broadcase)

rxFlowCtrlPram.description: Half duplex: Number of Flow Control collisions generated due to PRAM limitations. Full duplex: Number of MAC pause control frames transmitted due to PRAM limitations.

rxFlowCtrlNimbus.name: rxFlowCtrlNimbus
rxFlowCtrlNimbus.description: Half duplex: Number of Flow Control collisions generated due to NIMBUS overload. Full duplex: Number of MAC pause control frames transmitted due to NIMBUS overload.

rxPramOverRuns.description: Rx packets discarded due to PRAM limitation

rxNimbusOverRuns.name: rxNimbusOverRuns
rxNimbusOverRuns.description: Rx packets discarded due to NIMBUS limitation

rxVeryLongErrors.description: Rx packets that are much too long (> 6000 bytes).

rxLongErrors.name: rxLongErrors
rxLongErrors.description: Rx packets that are too long (> 1518 bytes)

rxPauseMacControlReceived.name: rxPauseMacControlReceived
rxPauseMacControlReceived.description: Number of MAC pause control frames received

rxUnknownMacControlFrame.description: Number of unsupported MAC control frames received

rxPiaOutOfPoolDropErrors.description: Reception is aborted due to lack of pool memory -- the switch is overloaded.

rxCodeViolations.description: An illegal symbol received on a 100Base-X port.

rxJabberErrors.description: Rx packets that are too long and contains CRC errors and/or dribble nibble.

rxNiaOverRunDropErrors.name: rxNiaOverRunDropErrors
rxNiaOverRunDropErrors.description: The NIA Rx buffer goes to overrun if the nimbus is overloaded (NIA10 only).

totalRxTxPackets.name: totalRxTxPackets
totalRxTxPackets.description: This object is used for LED control to display traffic. Values in the string are all packets transmitted and received at each port. The number and order of values equals the ifIndex, however only physical ports are included in the array. Each entry is 4 bytes. The first 4 bytes of the string is the value of portLastChange.

totalCollisions.name: totalCollisions
totalCollisions.description: This object is used for LED control to display collision. Values in the string are the total collisions at each port. The number and order of values equals the ifIndex, however only physical ports are included in the array. Each entry is 4 bytes. The first 4 bytes of the string is the value of portLastChange.

adaptiveForwardModeSampleTime.name: adaptiveForwardModeSampleTime
adaptiveForwardModeSampleTime.description: Specify how long (in seconds) the received packets will be monitored. The resulting forwarding mode will be based on the quality of the packets

adaptiveForwardModeRuntsOffset.name: adaptiveForwardModeRuntsOffset
adaptiveForwardModeRuntsOffset.description: Specifies the minimum amount of runts during the sample time which forces the port out of cutThrough(2). The value is specified in per mill * 1000

adaptiveForwardModeRuntsRange.name: adaptiveForwardModeRuntsRange
adaptiveForwardModeRuntsRange.description: Specifies (together with adaptiveForwardModeRuntsOffset) the maximum amount of runts allowed during the sample time. This forces the port back to cutThrough(2). The value is specified in per mill * 1000

adaptiveForwardModeCrcsOffset.name: adaptiveForwardModeCrcsOffset
adaptiveForwardModeCrcsOffset.description: Specifies the maximum amount of CRC errors during the sample time. This forces the port out of Store-and-Forward. The value is specified in per mill * 1000

adaptiveForwardModeCrcsRange.name: adaptiveForwardModeCrcsRange
adaptiveForwardModeCrcsRange.description: Specifies together with adaptiveForwardModeCrcsOffset the maximum amount of CRC errors during the sample time. This forces the port out of Store-and-Forward. The value is specified in per mill * 1000

permanentEntriesCreateObj.name: permanentEntriesCreateObj
permanentEntriesCreateObj.description: Create a non-existant table entry. If the entry already exists, genError is returned. Format: PortId (INTEGER)

matrixModuleTable.name: matrixModuleTable
matrixModuleTable.description: The table for general stack information

matrixModuleEntry.name: matrixModuleEntry
matrixModuleEntry.description: Information for a specific module slot about stackconnections, state, masterinformation

matrixModuleIndex.name: matrixModuleIndex
matrixModuleIndex.description: Slot number to retrieve information for. 1 is slot A, 2 is slot B

matrixModuleState.name: matrixModuleState
matrixModuleState.description: State of the matrix module. If notAvailable(99) no matrix module can be seen, active(1) is indicating a running module, standby(2) is indicating a module that is ready to become active if needed in a redundant setup, error(3) indicates a stack/redundancy error, back(4) is id the SIM module is running in a back to back configuration

matrixNumberConnected.name: matrixNumberConnected
matrixNumberConnected.description: The number of connected units to the matrix module

matrixMasterPort.name: matrixMasterPort
matrixMasterPort.description: 0 means no master available, otherwise an ifindex is returned (50->57)

matrixPortEntry.name: matrixPortEntry
matrixPortEntry.description: Per switch of information gathered from the matrix module about the connected devices

matrixPortModuleIndex.name: matrixPortModuleIndex
matrixPortModuleIndex.description: Slot number to retrieve information for. 1 is slot A, 2 is slot B

matrixPortIndex.name: matrixPortIndex
matrixPortIndex.description: Index for retrieving the matrix ports

matrixPort.name: matrixPort
matrixPort.description: 0 means no device is available, otherwise an ifindex is returned (50->57)

matrixPortType.name: matrixPortType
matrixPortType.description: The connected device type, notAvailable(99) if unknown or none

matrixPortMajVer.name: matrixPortMajVer
matrixPortMajVer.description: Major Version of matrix module shared memory layout supported

matrixPortMinVer.name: matrixPortMinVer
matrixPortMinVer.description: Minor Version of matrix module shared memory layout supported

matrixPortMac.name: matrixPortMac
matrixPortMac.description: Mac address of the device connected to a specific matrix port. If the device does not have a mac address it will be zero

matrixPortIp.name: matrixPortIp
matrixPortIp.description: IP address of the device connected to a specific matrix port. If the device does not have an IP address it will be zero

matrixPortSubnetMask.name: matrixPortSubnetMask
matrixPortSubnetMask.description: IP subnet mask of the device connected to a specific matrix port.

matrixPortGateway.name: matrixPortGateway
matrixPortGateway.description: IP gateway of the device connected to a specific matrix port.

matrixLastChange.name: matrixLastChange
matrixLastChange.description: Timestamp for last change in matrix tables on any Matrix module

mediaModuleEntry.name: mediaModuleEntry
mediaModuleEntry.description: Possible values of indices are 1..stackMaxChassis, 1..chassisMaxModules and 1..moduleMaxMediaModules

moduleMode.name: moduleMode

matrixAttachmentPort.name: matrixAttachmentPort
matrixAttachmentPort.description: Returns the port number of the Matrix port the uplink mmodule is attached to. NB: will return 50 for a uplink module not connected to a Matrix Module

mediaModuleChange.name: mediaModuleChange
mediaModuleChange.description: The value of sysUpTime after any mediamoduletype has changed

s500PermVioEvent.name: s500PermVioEvent
s500PermVioEvent.description: This trap is sent when there has been a permanent entry violation. A MAC address has been detected at a port, other than the port where it has been configured as a permanent entry. The variable portIfIndex indicates the port where the MAC incorrectly has been detected. The problem can be solved by re-configuring the MAC's permanent entry, or by physically moving the MAC to the port it has been configured for.

s500AdaptiveForwEvent.name: s500AdaptiveForwEvent
s500AdaptiveForwEvent.description: This trap is sent when a port automatically is changing forwarding mode. This will only happen when the port has been configured to Adaptive mode. The syntax is (Portnumber, New mode, Old mode)

s500TemperatureEvent.name: s500TemperatureEvent
s500TemperatureEvent.description: This trap indicates that the temparature of the chassis has changed

s500RedundantPowerSupplyEvent.name: s500RedundantPowerSupplyEvent
s500RedundantPowerSupplyEvent.description: This trap indicates that the status of the redundant power supply has changed
